thread.title: Aaron Rodgers calls his combine 40-yard dash time 'fake news'
thread.title_full: Aaron Rodgers calls his combine 40-yard dash time 'fake news'

author: Kirstie Chiappelli (kchiappelli@sportingnews.com)
title: Aaron Rodgers calls his combine 40-yard dash time 'fake news'
text:
NFL February 23, 2017 11:18am EST February 23, 2017 11:18am EST American Football, News, English, Aaron Rodgers, NFL, Green Bay Packers The Packers quarterback corrected the NFL after it tweet a photo of him running a 4.71 40-yard dash in Indianapolis 12 years ago. Aaron Rodgers (Getty Images) 
Updated at 11:18 a.m. ET 
Updated at 11:18 a.m. ET 
Aaron Rodgers wants everyone to know he can run faster than the NFL claims he can. 
With the combine less than a week away, the NFL on Wednesday tweeted a photo of the Packers quarterback running a 4.71 40-yard dash in Indianapolis 12 years ago. Rodgers responded Thursday and pointed out the time was actually 4.66.
